The paper deals with randomness extraction from sources with partial control by an adversary, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses distributed sources, which can be categorized under distributed systems (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper uses the notion of maximal correlation, which is a concept in coding theory (cs.CC).
